The paper discusses the use of neural networks for generating sequences with complex structures, specifically in the context of program generation. This falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of custom loss functions and optimization techniques, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper focuses on the use of logical machines to represent underlying grammars, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
